cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.CY

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and information retrieval (IR) techniques applied to electronic health records (EHRs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and text processing. The paper also involves the use of Elasticsearch, a search engine, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of the Observational Medical Outcomes Partnership (OMOP) Common Data Model (CDM) also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to improve cohort retrieval performance, which falls under the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
